owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:seeAlso: For detailed instructions on how to use see: https://coclass.byggtjanst.se/sv

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: comparableHaystack
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:seeAlso: For detaild descriptions of Haystack tags see: https://project-haystack.org/tag

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property to model nesting of building components, e.g., rooms within apartments or walls within stairwells, etc.
Inverse properties of the isPartOf property tree, used for top-down traversal of the parthood hierarchy.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has part

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A property that allows for nesting of devices within devices.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isPartOfDevice

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An object that can describe its place by using [object-UUID] locatedIn [myOtherObject-UUID], where [myOtherObject-UUID] could be a Room, BuildingStructure, etc.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isLocatedIn

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A generic clustering of meronomy (parthood) relations, allowing for the traversal of the parthood taxonomy of a real estate. Note that this is a transitive property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is part of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates which building a given building component is part of. Note that the parthood hierarchy is transitive, so every building component does not necessarily need to be invidiually connected to a building or a real estate; this can be inferred through the more generic isPartOf property.
Indicates that a building structure or a piece of land belongs to / is part of a given real estate.

For example an airtreatment device (Device) that serves several rooms (BuildingStructureComponent) or a full building (BuildingStructure). Can also be a Device (e.g. airtreatment device) serving another Device (e.g. air diffuser).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: serves

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Used to map an Id in an external system to an instance (e.g. an UUID).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasAliasID

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Extra information about an object that is of a more exceptional character (compared to Description). E.g. "This Device needs to be replaced no later than 2020", "Note: Black color is used to mark warmwater inlet"
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasComment

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Measured in ms (milli seconds). Duration is defined as the length of time that something lasts.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasDuration

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
The angle between one of the axis of a local coordinate system within e.g. a building and a north-south meridian. The angle is measured between the meridian and the local coordinate axis and counted as positive to the east side of the meridan (neagtive to the west side).
Bearings are never greater than 90°. Bearings are based on true north.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasGeoReferenceBearing

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
Linking to https://www.geonames.org
E.g. for Stockholm (Sweden): LocationUUID#1 hasGenonames http://www.geonames.org/2673730/stockholm.html
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasGeonames

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Designation or enumeration commenly found on blueprints for an object. E.g. text designating a Device or a Room.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasLittera

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Use this property to add [proprietary] regions.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasRegion

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Used for information about a source system or data.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasSource

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
Cognitive clustering of time-related properties that can apply to time-indexed objects (i.e., events of various sorts).
Certain time properties are given using xsd:DateTime, i.e., ISO8601 (see below), whereas others are given as ints or floats, depending on use case.
Time format ISO8601:
Complete date, hour, minutes, seconds, and decimal fraction of second
YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD (eg 1997-07-16T19:20:30.45+01:00)
Where: YYYY = 4 numbers for year. MM = 2 numbers for month (01=January, etc.) DD = 2 numbers for day of month (01 till 31) hh = 2 numbers for hour (00 till 23) (am/pm not allowed) mm = 2 numbers for minutes (00 till 59) ss = 2 numbers for second (00 till 59) s = 1 or more numbers represent a decimal fraction of second
TZD = time zone designator (Z or +hh:mm or -hh:mm) Time is expressed in UTC (Coordinated Universal Time), with designated UTC ("Z") for GMT.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasTime

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: If a Location has multiple visiting addresses, then just add as many hasVistingAddress as needed.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasVistingAddress

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An object that has an exact point (expressed in WGS84 in decimal degrees as (latitude,longitude,altitude).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: isLocatedAt

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Literal value in meter (x,y,z) in a local coordinate system that referes to GeoReferenceOrigo.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: isLocatedAtLocalCoordinates

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The human or machine that consumes or acts upon an object or data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The parts that makes up a building structure (Building). E.g., Room, Facade, RoofInner, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Building component

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A thing made or adapted for a particular purpose, specifically a piece of electronic equipment. A Device has one or more Sensor(s) and/or Actuator(s).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Device

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A fixed point for e.g. a building structure. Commonly refered to as "insertion point" in CAD-programs. Used as origo for LocalCoordinates.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeoReferenceOrigo

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The land where one or more buildings are situated.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Land

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
A Location must have either a spatial relation to another location (e.g. "contained in"), a geographical coordinate representing its centre, or a pair of geographical coordintes representing it's outer boundaries (northwest/southeast)
An instance of Location can have a PopularName and isLocatedAt a geographical point.
E.g. Defining Stockholm as a Location: LocationUUID#1 isA Location LocationUUID#1 hasPopularName "Stockholm" LocationUUID#1 isLocatedAt (59.333683,18.068579,0) LocationUUID#1 isLocatedIn LocationUUID#2
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Location

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
The measurment units that are used in RealEstateCore. Use SI-units in general. Store values without prefixes.
Exceptions to SI: Express temperature in Celsius, Energy in Watt hour (Wh), Angle i degrees (360 degress = 1 revolution) MillimeterPerHour for Precipation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Measurement unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describes the type of values that can be observed by sensors or set by actuators. Inspired by QUDT.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quantity kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Types of objects that can make up a piece of real estate, e.g., land and buildings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Real estate component

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: When a human interacts with a system. E.g. pushes a button to turn on/off a light, force ventilation.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: AgentInteraction
AlarmSevere
owl:NamedIndividual.comparableBIP: H1B1xx, H1B4xx, H1B5xx, H1B9xx, H1B6xx, H1B3xx, H1B7xx H1B2xx, H1B9xx

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Temperature in Celsius degress. Note that correct SI Unit is Kelvin.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Celsius

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The angle between two electrical phases.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: CosPhi

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Volume is the quantity of three-dimensional space enclosed by a closed surface, for example, the space that a substance (solid, liquid, gas, or plasma) or shape occupies or contains. Volume is often quantified numerically using the cubic metre (m3).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: CubicMeter

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Total energy (not specified as Active or Reactive, used for e.g. district heating).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: EnergyTotal

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Light intensity in a specific area.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Lux

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The pascal is the SI derived unit of pressure used to quantify internal pressure, stress. It is defined as one newton per square metre.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Pascal
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:seeAlso: In Haystack: barometric is described as "Defines the mean atmospheric pressure at sea level measured in millibar or in Hg."

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The power factor of an AC electrical power system is defined as the ratio of the real power flowing to the load to the apparent power in the circuit, and is a dimensionless number in the closed interval of −1 to 1.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: PowerFactor

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Relative Humidity. The amount of water vapour present in air expressed as a percentage of the amount needed for saturation at the same temperature.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: RelativeHumidity

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The second is the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the cesium 133 atom.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Second

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Area unit. It is the area of a square whose sides measure exactly one metre.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: SquareMeter

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Voltage, electric potential difference, is the difference in electric potential between two points.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Volt

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This unit is typically used to express the momentaneous output power of engines and the power of electric motors, tools, machines, and heaters.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Watt
